GNU APL Font
============

The font file GNU_APL.ttf distributed here is a derived work of the BQN386
font by dzaima, cloned from:

    https://github.com/dzaima/BQN386.git

on 2026-06-15.

The following modifications were made to add and fix glyphs required for
GNU APL on Windows (MinGW/cmd.exe):

  - Added glyph U+2208 (∈, element-of / epsilon)
  - Added glyph U+2297 (⊗, circle-times, constructed as an overstrike
    of the asterisk U+2217 inside the circle ring, matching the APL
    overstrike convention used for U+235F ⍟)
  - Cleared advance-width rounding hints from glyphs U+2223 (∣),
    U+2282 (⊂), U+2283 (⊃), U+20AC (€), U+222A (∪), U+22A5 (⊥)
    to ensure uniform one-column display width in Windows console

